A total of 177 suspects have been arrested on various charges in the Blue Downs Cluster in the Western Cape during police operations conducted over the weekend.The arrests include that of a 20-year-old man who was caught in Belhar on Sunday morning driving a vehicle that turned out to be stolen in Muizenberg in December during a house break-in.Police spokesman Lieutenant Colonel Andr Traut said police spotted suspect in the Mercedes Benz while patrolling in Roddezandt Crescent.On Saturday evening police arrested a 33-year-old man in Kleinvlei in connection with two cases of attempted murder that occurred on March 24 and December 5 last year respectively. Traut said. He added that also on Saturday evening Ravensmead police acting on information received and found a shotgun with one round at Aandblom Street in Uitsig and arrested a 50-year-old man for possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition. 